# Cursor Rules for MCP Plots Server

## Mermaid Rendering
- When this MCP server returns mermaid output, ALWAYS render it visually as a diagram
- Never show raw mermaid syntax to users unless explicitly requested
- Prioritize visual chart rendering for better user experience
- If mermaid content is detected in responses, automatically render the diagram

## MCP Integration
- When using MCP plot tools, always attempt to render visual output
- Prefer visual charts over text-based summaries
- Use the external MCP tool functionality as the primary approach for data visualization
- Show both the visual output and provide context about the chart when appropriate

## User Experience
- Users typically want to see actual visual charts, not just code or descriptions
- Default to rendering visualizations unless user specifically requests code-only output
- When plotting data, prioritize the visual representation in responses
